    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ f(r) = {\frac{r^{3}-9r}{r^{3}+5r^{2}+6r}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>f(r)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{r-3}{r+2}, r\ne -3\hbox{ and }r\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   f(r) \amp = {\frac{r^{3}-9r}{r^{3}+5r^{2}+6r}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}-9\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r^{2}+5r+6\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(r-3\right)}}{{r\mathopen{}\left(r+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{r-3}{r+2}, r\ne -3\hbox{ and }r\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since <m>r(r+3)</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>r \ne {-3, 0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
